<p>
Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj (1630-1680) was a legendary 17th-century Maratha warrior king<br>
who founded the Maratha Empire in western India.Born at Shivneri Fort, he pioneered guerrilla<br>
warfare ("Ganimi Kava"), established a formidable navy,and challenged the Mughal Empire,<br>
establishing an independent Hindu kingdom, or Hindavi Swarajya, coronated in 1674.<br>
</p>

<p>
The 17th-century king's legacy is honored today, with the landmark <br>
railway station in Mumbai known as the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Terminus (CSMT).<br>

<p>
Known as a just and progressive ruler, he was a secular leader who respected<br>
all religions and championed women's rights
